68px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3408x2265+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F05%2Fac%2Faf810db2472fbefc6e7ec8697d57%2Fgettyimages-848677744.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3408x2265+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F05%2Fac%2Faf810db2472fbefc6e7ec8697d57%2Fgettyimages-848677744.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3408x2265+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F05%2Fac%2Faf810db2472fbefc6e7ec8697d57%2Fgettyimages-848677744.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3408x2265+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F05%2Fac%2Faf810db2472fbefc6e7ec8697d57%2Fgettyimages-848677744.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3408x2265+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F05%2Fac%2Faf810db2472fbefc6e7ec8697d57%2Fgettyimages-848677744.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3408x2265+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F05%2Fac%2Faf810db2472fbefc6e7ec8697d57%2Fgettyimages-848677744.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3408x2265+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F05%2Fac%2Faf810db2472fbefc6e7ec8697d57%2Fgettyimages-848677744.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3408x2265+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F05%2Fac%2Faf810db2472fbefc6e7ec8697d57%2Fgettyimages-848677744.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3408x2265+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F05%2Fac%2Faf810db2472fbefc6e7ec8697d57%2Fgettyimages-848677744.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3408x2265+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F05%2Fac%2Faf810db2472fbefc6e7ec8697d57%2Fgettyimages-848677744.jpg" class="img" alt="Lorne Michaels poses with his Emmy for Outstanding Variety/Sketch Series in 2017." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Lorne Michaels poses with his Emmy for Outstanding Variety/Sketch Series in 2017.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Alberto E. Rodriguez/Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Now age 80, Michaels' advancing years raises a powerful question: Who else can muster the balance of show business power and managerial savvy to keep &lt;em&gt;SNL&lt;/em&gt; going after him?&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Morrison has heard the popular names floated as successors, like Tina Fey and Seth Meyers (Meyers gets my vote, particularly if Michaels steps back at a time when NBC might consider ending his show &lt;em&gt;Late Night&lt;/em&gt;). But she's not sure anyone could truly pull it off.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;"The thing is, so much of the show has to do with his mystique, you know, his unpredictable Wizard of Oz-ness," she adds of Michaels, who she says can be cryptic and hands off as a manager until Saturday, when tough decisions must come over what airs that night. "He seems to me like the most powerful executive at NBC … In terms of a Lorne-free &lt;em&gt;SNL&lt;/em&gt;, that's kind of hard for me to see."&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Yet Michaels — and SNL — has also made mistakes.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;It didn't reflect America's racial diversity for far too long&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;p&gt;One of the saddest ironies of Jason Reitman's uneven film &lt;em&gt;Saturday Night&lt;/em&gt; — a look in real-time at the 90 minutes before the show's first telecast on Oct. 11, 1975 — is Lamorne Morris' masterful depiction of the show's first Black cast member, Garrett Morris (no relation). Almost all his screen time features Morris pleading with the show's producers to actually use him in a sketch. Instead, he sings a song for the cast and crew at a rehearsal before the actual telecast, proving his worth in a way no TV viewers would see that night.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-47824" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 3000;         --source-height: 2059;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x2059+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe5%2F75%2F5913b8df4f24b98f23fbdcd1ea7c%2Fap8402100120.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x2059+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe5%2F75%2F5913b8df4f24b98f23fbdcd1ea7c%2Fap8402100120.jpg 600w, https://npr.